post_text:
Hello Parents and Guardians of Zuni Public School District,

The tribe has installed 5 access points within the village, they are located at:

1.) ZHS Football Field parking lot
2.) Zuni Tribal Building
3.) Zuni Public Library
4.) Halona Marketplace
5.) Halona Plaza

The name of the broadcast signal is HomeworkHub (there is no password to join).

Also there are three access points located in the District:

1.) ZHS Parking lot
2.) TBCA/CO Admin parking lot
3.) ZMS Tennis Court parking lot.

These access points were setup for students to utilize for online learning. Please practice social distancing and adhere to the curfew.

**All ZPSD students are welcome to use these free hotspots.

post_text:
Hello Parents and Guardians,

This is a message regarding the Kajeet Hotspots with the model number SA 2100. These Kajeet hotspots will need to be returned back to the schools that they were checked out from, in the original box that they came in. The model numbers are located on the bottom of the Kajeets. These Kajeet Hotspots are using a network that is not available in Zuni. Also, if you have requested more than one device for the household, please return the additional ones, back to the schools. At this point, we only have enough for one per household. These devices should only be used for educational purposes and are not intended to be used for entertainment. Hours of usage are restricted and are not available between the hours of 11 pm and 6 am. Any questions or concerns please contact your child's school site administrators.

Thank you and stay safe.

shared_text:
Zuni Middle School
August 9 at 5:26 PM ·

Please see the letter from Mr. Lewis, ZMS Principal, as well as the virtual period schedule.

On your student schedule:
M-F is daily class Monday through Friday.
M-TH is daily class Monday through Thursday.
M, W means class is only on Monday and Wednesday.
T, TH means class is only on Tuesday and Thursday.

Students start the day in Crew daily Monday through Friday for 40 minutes.
Core classes: Math, ELA, Science, and Social Studies are twice a week, each session 60 minutes.
Zuni L & C is daily Monday through Thursday for 45 minutes.
Electives (Creative Art, PE, and Study Skills) are twice a week, each session for 30 minutes.

Science 7 and Study Skills (Strategies for Success) will be online through Edgenuity.

Any questions or concerns do not hesitate to ask us!!

Parents and Guardians of Zuni Middle School,

On behalf of the Math team we are requesting you to come pick up resource materials needed for the first quarter. The drive thru pick up will happen on Friday, August 7th starting at 10:30 at the ZMS main entrance loop located by our main entrance. This will be a drive thru pick up so you will not have to get out of your vehicle, masks should still be worn to align to social distancing practices.

We thank you for your ongoing collaboration and look forward to working with you all. If you have any questions please feel free to contact us at the school or email Ms. Byrum at renee.byrum@zpsd.org.

An important message from the Zuni Middle School Staff:

Hello Zuni Middle School parents. We will start distributing Chromebooks and other school supplies this week.

Wednesday, August 5th will be designated for 6th and 7th grade pickup. There will be two time options, 10:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m. and 5:00 p.m. - 6:00 p.m.

Thursday, August 6th will be designated for 8th grade pick up. There will be two time options, 10:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m. and 5:00 p.m. - 6:00 p.m.

User agreement forms must be signed upon pickup so one parent and the student must be present. Please limit visitors to these guidelines. Make sure you wear a mask and practice social distancing as you are waiting in line.

IF YOU HAVE NOT REGISTERED YOUR STUDENT(S) PLEASE DO SO AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

SCHOOL STARTS AUGUST 10, 2020!!!!

Thank you!

Board President Vicenti, would like to Congratulate Lashawna Weahkee for receiving the New Mexico School Board Association Scholarship Award. An all-around scholar, Lashawna exemplifies the qualities of a leader who continually looks for new opportunities to learn and grow as a continued leader in our Zuni community. On behalf of the Board of Education, I would like to wish her the best as she continues to further her education! Congratulations Lashawna!

**LaShawna is the second recipient of this award for Zuni Public School District!**

Hello, Parents and Guardians of a current and future Zuni Middle School student.

Zuni Middle School registration is now available electronically.

You can access the link by visiting the District’s Homepage at zpsd.org.

If you do not have internet access you can visit the school either on Monday, June 1st from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m., Tuesday, June 2nd from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m., or from 1 p.m. to 3 p.m., and Thursday, June 4th from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. to register on one of the school's computers.

Thank you and stay healthy.

Attention ZPSD Students, Parents, and Guardians.

WiFi access points have been set up for students in accessing their online classes. Access points are set up on the East side of the ZHS parking lot/AEP portable. This is a temporary setup for students while waiting to get WiFi installed on Buses. ZPSD students are welcome to utilize the access points with the practice of social distancing and adhere to the nightly curfew. For any technical difficulties please contact the school site administrator. Thank you.

post_text: 80+ of our Zuni youth from Zuni Middle School and Zuni High School took part in the Inter-Tribal Youth Summit hosted by the COPE program and ZYEP. This Summit was a great opportunity for our Zuni youth to get out and see their abilities as leaders within our community. It was also a great experience for them to meet other indigenous youth from the nations of Alaska, South Dakota, Hawaii, and New Mexico.
